definition: Santiago, capital of Chile/San Diego, California
-ly/structural particle: used before a verb or adjective, linking it to preceding modifying adverbial adjunct

sentences.english: Cambodians and other groups in San Diego were in a similar situation.
sentences.chinese: 圣地亚哥的柬埔寨人和其他团体也处于同样境地。

sentences.english: Chinese ammunitions enterprises regularly attend the Santiago Air Show every two years.
sentences.chinese: 中国弹药企业每两年一次定期参加圣地亚哥航空展。

sentences.english: We like to spend a lot of time in San Diego.
sentences.chinese: 我们喜欢在圣地亚哥呆很久。

sentences.english: San Diego State University is a 5-minute drive away.
sentences.chinese: 圣地亚哥国际机场距离酒店有5分钟车程。

sentences.english: But Raúl had no such announcements to make in Santiago.
sentences.chinese: 但是，劳尔在圣地亚哥的演说中并没有这样的声明。

sentences.english: I find that San Francisco is a lot more liberal than San Diego.
sentences.chinese: 我发现旧金山比圣地亚哥更为自由。

sentences.english: And look, I can see my breath, and we’re in San Diego.
sentences.chinese: 而且你看，我能看到我的呼吸，我们还在圣地亚哥。

sentences.english: Best wishes to all. We'll see each other tomorrow at the Santiago Bernabeu Stadium.
sentences.chinese: 祝福所有人，我们明天将在圣地亚哥伯纳乌球场见面。

sentences.english: So it's very different than San Diego.
sentences.chinese: 所以说跟圣地亚哥很不一样。

sentences.english: In 1553 Havana became the capital of Cuba instead of Santiago de Cuba.
sentences.chinese: 1553年取代圣地亚哥成为古巴首都。

sentences.english: Does the express train stop at San Diego?
sentences.chinese: 这班特快车停靠圣地亚哥吗？

sentences.english: It is a great pleasure to meet with our old and new friends in the beautiful city of San Diego.
sentences.chinese: 很高兴在美丽的圣地亚哥与各位新老朋友见面。

sentences.english: Garcia was transported to the custody of the San Diego Sheriff's Department.
sentences.chinese: 后来加西亚被押送至圣地亚哥监护所。

sentences.english: Coffee bars will only work in Santiago, because Chileans are so uptight.
sentences.chinese: 咖啡馆只有在圣地亚哥才能经营，因为这里太保守了。

sentences.english: Santiago de Compostela was an important place of pilgrimage in the Middle Ages.
sentences.chinese: 中世纪圣地亚哥一德孔波斯特拉是朝圣的要地。

sentences.english: The missions begin with San Diego de Alcala in the south.
sentences.chinese: 这些任务首先圣地亚哥德阿尔卡拉在南部。

definition: (Tw) San Diego, California/Santiago, capital of Chile
